inges%20on%20something%20you%20didn't%20mention%20in%20your%20letter.%20When%20you%20gave%20your%20son%20the%20%2416%2C000%20eight%20years%20ago%2C%20did%20you%20call%20it%20a%20gift%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Floans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloan%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20You%20said%20you%20gave%20your%20son%20%26quot%3Bthe%20money%20with%20no%20strings%2C%26quot%3B%20implying%20you%20originally%20intended%20it%20to%20be%20a%20gift.%20But%20you%20also%20mention%20that%20your%20son%20has%20already%20paid%20back%20%246000%2C%20so%20perhaps%20you%20both%20always%20understood%20he%20would%20eventually%20need%20to%20repay%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20clear%20with%20your%20son%20from%20the%20beginning%20that%20this%20money%20was%20a%20loan%2C%20he%20knows%20what%20he%20must%20do.%20He's%20an%20adult%2C%20and%20while%20he's%20lucky%20his%20lender%20is%20a%20forgiving%20and%20flexible%20parent%2C%20that%20doesn't%20change%20the%20fact%20this%20was%20never%20his%20money%20to%20keep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20is%20the%20case%2C%20I%20would%20sit%20down%20with%20your%20son%20and%20build%20a%20manageable%20payment%20plan%20that%20won't%20financially%20hurt%20his%20growing%20family.%20Asking%20your%20son%20to%20pay%20you%20back%20this%20way%20may%20feel%20awkward%20and%20cruel%2C%20but%20remember%20that%20you're%20challenging%20him%20to%20follow%20through%20on%20his%20commitments.%20An%20integrity%20that%20will%20only%20make%20him%20a%20stronger%2C%20better%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20however%2C%20by%20%26quot%3Bno%20strings%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20mean%20the%20money%20was%20a%20gift%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20just%20that%20you%20wrote%20a%20check%20to%20your%20son%20without%20giving%20any%20verbal%20expectation%20of%20repayment%20%E2%80%94%20this%20dilemma%20is%20now%20a%20question%20of%20your%20integrity.%20%2416%2C000%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20When%20a%20parent%20gives%20you%20such%20a%20large%20sum%20to%20help%20you%20out%20of%20a%20jam%2C%20unless%20they%20say%20otherwise%2C%20you%20don't%20assume%20they%20plan%20to%20burden%20your%20future%20with%20an%20expectation%20of%20repayment.%20Parents%20give%20their%20kids%20gifts%20from%20day%20one%20on%20the%20planet.%20So%2C%20while%20this%20assumption%20may%20be%20entitled%2C%20it's%20honestly%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20financially%20burdening%20your%20child's%20future%2C%20a%20%2416%2C000%20loan%20is%20significant.%20I'm%20in%20my%20mid-30s%20with%20a%20secure%20and%20comfortable%20income.%20And%20still%2C%20I%20will%20take%20my%20time%20and%20do%20my%20due%20diligence%20before%20borrowing%20that%20amount%20of%20money%20for%20a%20car%20loan.%20I%20would%20certainly%20be%20concerned%20if%20a%20young%20relative%20told%20me%20they%20were%20taking%20on%20%2416%2C000%20worth%20of%20debt.%20Now%2C%20your%20son%20was%20going%20through%20a%20divorce%2C%20so%20he%20wasn't%20a%20child%2C%20and%20I%20wouldn't%20judge%20you%20for%20offering%20him%20an%20interest-free%20loan%20as%20long%20as%20he%20knew%20it%20was%20a%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20me%20to%20the%20other%20point%20your%20letter%20didn't%20specify%20%E2%80%94%20where%20was%20your%20husband%20eight%20years%20ago%20when%20you%20gave%20your%20son%20this%20money%3F%20Perhaps%20he%20wasn't%20in%20the%20picture%20yet%2C%20or%20maybe%20he%20was%20around%20and%20agreed%20with%20your%20choice%20to%20give%20your%20son%20the%20money.%20Or%2C%20you%20knew%20your%20husband%20would%20make%20an%20issue%20out%20of%20it%2C%20so%20you%20chose%20not%20to%20tell%20him%20you%20were%20giving%20your%20son%20money%20since%20it%20was%20your%20money%20to%20give.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20of%20these%20scenarios%20I%20listed%2C%20your%20husband%20can%20have%20an%20opinion%2C%20but%20since%20it%20wasn't%20his%20money%20then%20or%20now%2C%20he%20doesn't%20get%20to%20decide%20how%20you%20handle%20this%20with%20your%20son.%20That%20said%2C%20if%20you%20hid%20your%20choice%20to%20give%20your%20son%20money%20from%20your%20husband%20eight%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20has%20every%20right%20to%20be%20upset%2C%20even%20if%20he%20agrees%20that%20the%20money%20was%20yours%20alone.%20Unless%20you're%20multi-millionaires%2C%20%2416%2C000%20is%20a%20large%20sum%2C%20and%20doing%20anything%20with%20such%20a%20hefty%20chunk%20of%20cash%20certainly%20falls%20under%20the%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20partner%20about%20this%20first%26quot%3B%20umbrella.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20is%20the%20emotional%20half%20of%20our%20marriage.%20He%20frets%20and%20fumes%20whenever%20his%20feelings%20call%20for%20it.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20I%20can't%20bear%20the%20drama%20of%20big%20emotions%2C%20not%20for%20myself%20or%20anyone%20else%20around%20me.%20When%20I%20find%20myself%20in%20a%20situation%20I%20know%20will%20upset%20my%20husband%2C%20hiding%20it%20is%20always%20my%20first%20impulse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it's%20a%20broken%20household%20appliance%20or%20one%20of%20our%20children%20needing%20something%20expensive%20that%20I%20worry%20he%20won't%20consider%20a%20%26quot%3Bneed%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20it%20my%20way%20%E2%80%94%20stoically%20%E2%80%94%20while%20he%20remains%20blissfully%20unbothered.%20Omitting%20these%20concerns%20may%20keep%20my%20heart%20beating%20at%20a%20comfortable%2C%20steady%20tempo%2C%20but%20deep%20down%2C%20I%20know%20I%20have%20to%20let%20him%20know%20what's%20going%20on%20because%20teamwork%20requires%20honest%20communication.%20Unless%20I%20do%20the%20hard%20thing%20and%20talk%20to%20him%2C%20I'm%20setting%20us%20both%20up%20for%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recognize%20a%20similar%20tension%20in%20your%20letter.%20Your%20deepest%20concern%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20getting%20your%20%2410%2C000%20back%3B%20instead%2C%20the%20friction%20the%20money%20is%20causing%20between%20your%20son%20and%20your%20husband%20bothers%20you.%20You%20even%20said%20that%20as%20far%20as%20you're%20concerned%2C%20you%20gave%20your%20son%20%26quot%3Bthe%20money%20with%20no%20strings%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20since%20your%20husband%20disagrees%2C%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20you%20find%20yourself%20caught%20between%20two%20people%20you%20love%20who%20aren't%20afraid%20to%20ask%20you%20to%20give%20them%20their%20way%20at%20the%20other's%20expense.%20And%20in%20case%20you%20need%20someone%20to%20say%20it%2C%20I%20will%20%E2%80%94%20this%20isn't%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20can't%20tell%20you%20who%20to%20choose%2C%20I%20will%20tell%20you%20not%20to%20base%20your%20decision%20on%20which%20man%20you're%20more%20afraid%20of%20disappointing.%20Instead%2C%20reread%20your%20letter%20from%20my%20perspective.%20Try%20and%20see%20the%20situation%20through%20the%20eyes%20of%20someone%20without%20a%20shred%20of%20skin%20in%20the%20game.%20Ask%20yourself%20what%20you%20would%20tell%20the%20author%20of%20this%20letter%20to%20do.%20Do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERooting%20for%20you%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELooking%20for%20advice%20on%20how%20your%20savings%2C%20debt%2C%20or%20another%20financial%20challenge%20is%20affecting%20your%20relationships%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors