gcaption%3EApple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20could%20see%20a%20major%20revenue%20source%20threatened%20by%20Google's%20antitrust%20loss.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20federal%20judge%20ruled%20against%20Google%20in%20a%20major%20antitrust%20case.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20a%20loser%2C%20too.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat's%20because%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20case%20was%20about%20exclusive%20search%20deals%20Google%20does%20with%20Apple%20and%20other%20platform%20owners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle's%20Apple%20deal%20is%20worth%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20%2420%20billion%20in%202022%20alone.%20What%20happens%20if%20it%20goes%20away%2C%20or%20has%20to%20shrink%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20just%20ruled%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20major%20antitrust%20case.%20Apple%20could%20be%20caught%20in%20the%20blowback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-violated-antitrust-law-to-keep-search-monopoly-judge-rules-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment's%20case%20against%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20has%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20in%20search%20%E2%80%94%20focuses%20on%20deals%20Google%20makes%20with%20platforms%20and%20device-makers%20to%20be%20their%20default%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20biggest%20one%20of%20those%20is%20the%20one%20Apple%20has%20with%20Google%2C%20where%20Google%20pays%20Apple%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-apple-iphone-search-engine-safari-deal-20-billion-2022-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2420%20billion%20in%202022%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20have%20pole%20position%20on%20the%20iPhone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Amit%20P.%20Mehta's%20ruling%2C%20which%20holds%20that%20those%20deals%20are%20inhibiting%20competition%2C%20doesn't%20include%20his%20remedy.%20And%20Google%20says%20it%20plans%20to%20appeal%20his%20decision%20regardless.%20But%20if%20the%20ruling%20is%20ultimately%20upheld%2C%20and%20requires%20Google%20to%20stop%20making%20exclusive%20search%20deals%2C%20then%20it%20could%20threaten%20what's%20become%20an%20incredibly%20lucrative%20revenue%20stream%20for%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20this%20process%20continues%2C%20we%20will%20remain%20focused%20on%20making%20products%20that%20people%20find%20helpful%20and%20easy%20to%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20Kent%20Walker%2C%20Google's%20top%20lawyer%20and%20public%20policy%20executive%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20I've%20asked%20Apple%20for%20comment%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20is%20so%20giant%20%E2%80%94%20it%20generated%20nearly%20%24400%20billion%20in%20revenue%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20that%20even%20a%20%2420%20billion%20deal%20may%20not%20seem%20like%20that%20much%20to%20the%20company.%20And%20that%20number%20likely%20won't%20go%20to%20zero.%20Whether%20Google%20gets%20replaced%20by%20a%20competitor%20like%20Bing%2C%20or%20if%20it%20keeps%20working%20with%20iPhone%20but%20under%20different%20terms%2C%20Apple%20will%20still%20likely%20be%20able%20to%20get%20very%20good%20money%20leasing%20out%20real%20estate%20on%20its%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-advertising-google-search-services-filings-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20existing%20Google%20deal%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20Apple's%20%26quot%3Bservices%26quot%3B%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20as%20we've%20pointed%20out%20many%20times%2C%20growing%20its%20high-margin%20services%20revenue%20has%20become%20crucial%20for%20Apple%20as%20it