emotions%20as%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221693%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rhaenyra%20Targaryen%20and%20Alicent%20Hightower%20hugging%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66afabbfb4912df3ae18c848%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221270%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERhaenyra%20Targaryen%20and%20Alicent%20Hightower%20were%20close%20as%20children%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0as%20adults%2C%20not%20so%20much.%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOlivia%20did%20such%20a%20wonderful%20job%20in%20that%20moment%20where%20she%20started%20biting%20her%20nails.%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20such%20a%20great%20move%20on%20her%20part.%20I%20thought%20Emma's%20facial%20expressions%20became%20juvenile%20at%20moments%2C%20because%20they%20weren't%20presidential%20in%20this%20room.%20They%20were%20two%20girls.%20So%20that%20kind%20of%20thing%20is%20fun%20in%20that%20it's%20not%20on%20the%20page%2C%20it's%20in%20between%20the%20lines.%20And%20yet%20it%20was%20fully%20intended%20by%20Ryan%20and%20Sara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20season%20one%20it%20was%20the%20same%20thing.%20I%20had%20episode%20eight%2C%20season%20one%2C%20and%20there%20were%20dinner%20scenes%2C%20scenes%20about%20everything%2C%20but%20the%20one%20thing%20we%20didn't%20have%20a%20scene%20about%20was%20a%20scene%20between%20Rhaenyra%20and%20Alicent%20where%20they%20actually%20talked%20about%20how%20they%20were%20upset%20with%20each%20other%2C%20how%20they%20couldn't%20make%20amends.%20There%20was%20something%20at%20the%20very%20end%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20thinking%20of%20you.%20I%20hate%20you.%26quot%3B%20So%20we%20had%20to%20create%20that%20throughout%20that%20episode.%20Cinematographer%20Catherine%20Goldschmidt%20and%20I%20really%20sat%20down%20and%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20how%20can%20we%20put%20each%20of%20them%20in%20the%20room%20of%20the%20other%3F%26quot%3B%20So%20really%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20fun%20thing%20to%20do%20in%20filmmaking%2C%20because%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20things%20about%20the%20show%20that's%20super%20interesting%20is%20that%20there's%20very%20little%2C%20if%20any%2C%20exposition.%20It%20has%20to%20come%20out%20in%20the%20air.%20And%20the%20writing%20is%20so%20charged%20that%20you%20know%20there's%20a%20history%20behind%20what%20they're%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Olivia%20Cooke%20as%20Alicent%20and%20Emma%20D'Arcy%20as%20Rhaenyra%20in%20front%20of%20multiple%20candles%20in%20a%20dark%20room.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c4df8098114dafd1a73e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERhaenyra%20(Emma%20D'Arcy)%20visits%20her%20stepmother%2C%20Alicent%20(Olivia%20Cooke)%20in%20season%20two%2C%20episode%20three%20of%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20they%20can%20stop%20the%20brewing%20civil%20war.%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%20%2F%20HBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20two%20of%20them%20come%20to%20that%20room%2C%20the%20other%20thing%20that%20was%20really%20important%20is%20that%20the%20scene%20we%20had%20worked%20together%20on%20in%20episode%20three%20was%20the%20very%20last%20scene%20they'd%20had%20together.%20And%20that%20scene%20in%20episode%20eight%2C%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20needed%20to%20be%20immediately%20after%20that%20scene%20from%20episode%20three%20in%20their%20emotional%20minds.%20So%20Rhaenyra%20feels%20as%20if%20Alicent%20just%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20room%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20talk%20to%20you.%20Talk%20to%20the%20hand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20Alicent%20walks%20in%20and%20is%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20see%20Rhaenyra%20toughen%20up%2C%20and%20you%20see%20her%20almost%20wanting%20to%20spit%20on%20Alicent%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20dare%20you%20treat%20me%20the%20way%20you%20treated%20me%20last%20scene.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDaemon%20has%20been%20having%20a%20delightful%20time%20in%20Harrenhal%20with%20his%20horrible%20visions%20all%20season.%20The%20one%20that%20he%20has%20in%20this%20episode%20has%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20Daemon%20willingly%20back%20into%20Rhaenyra's%20fold.%20How%20did%20you%20want%20to%20stage%20that%2C%20and%20how%20did%20you%20work%20with%20Matt%20Smith%20on%20the%20scene%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20sleep%20over%20that%20stuff%2C%20because%20I%20read%20the%20script%2C%20and%20at%20the%20time%20the%20vision%20is%20written%20as%20you've%20got%20all%20these%20images%20that%20are%20striking%20and%20interesting.%20And%20that%20vision%20%E2%80%94%20very%20much%20through%20the%20visuals%20of%20it%20and%20the%20way%20it's%20cut%20together%20and%20the%20way%20it%20emotes%2C%20because%20it's%20wordless%20%E2%80%94%20that%20vision%20has%20to%20shift%20Daemon%20off%20of%20this%20track%20he's%20been%20on%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20get%20him%20to%20bend%20the%20knee%20to%20Rhaenyra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22matt%20smith%20as%20daemon%20targaryen%20in%20the%20season%20two%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20of%20the%20dragon.%26quot%3B%20he's%20wearing%20all%20black%20with%20his%20hair%20worn%20long%2C%20blonde%20and%20half%20back%2C%20and%20has%20a%20hand%20on%20the%20hilt%20of%20his%20sword.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66afabee393cd3c8629b2edd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Smith%20as%20Daemon%20Targaryen%20in%20the%20season%20two%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20I%20felt%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20healthy%20pressure%20making%20sure%20that%20we%20delivered%20what%20Ryan%20wanted%20for%20that%2C%20and%20what%20Sarah%20wanted%20for%20that.%20I%20spoke%20with%20them%20at%20length%2C%20and%20understood%20that%20Daemon%20needed%20to%20be%20convinced%20through%20the%20vision%20that%20Rhaenyra%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20on%20the%20throne.%20It%20didn't%20have%20to%20be%20crystal%20clear%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20vision%2C%20but%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20clear%2C%20and%20make%20sense%2C%20and%20earned%20by%20the%20time%20he%20got%20on%20his%20knees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20about%20this%20show%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20shows%20I've%20worked%20on%2C%20is%20point%20of%20view.%20There's%20people%20talking%20about%20people%20experiencing%20things%2C%20but%20there's%20always%20a%20choice%20of%20whose%20point%20of%20view%20you're%20in.%20And%20with%20Daemon%2C%20knowing%20that%20he%20had%20to%20bend%20the%20knee%20later%2C%20we%20had%20to%20really%20walk%20with%20him%20in%20this%20episode.%20We%20had%20to%20be%20in%20his%20point%20of%20view%2C%20because%20when%20he%20bent%20that%20knee%2C%20we%20had%20to%20feel%20what%20he%20was%20feeling%20in%20order%20to%20believe%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20had%20the%20bending%20of%20the%20knee%2C%20Matt%20and%20I%20spent%20many%20conversations%20thinking%20about%20how%20Daemon%20is%20a%20powerful%20character%2C%20powerful%20person%2C%20and%20he%20shouldn't%20feel%20weak%20in%20that%20scene.%20And%20so%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20I%20thought%20he%20did%20so%20beautifully%20was%20taking%20charge%20as%20her%20mentor%20in%20the%20hero's%20journey.%20Not%20mentor%20as%20in%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20man%2C%20you're%20a%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20mentor%20in%20the%20classic%20sense%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20wise%20soul.%20I%20have%20seen%20something.%20I%20know%20what's%20coming%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20in%20you%2C%20Rhaenyra.%20So%20stand%20up%20straight%2C%20put%20your%20shoulders%20back.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20pretend.%20You%20are%20who%20you%20need%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20what%20we%20talked%20about%2C%20because%20the%20big%20fear%20I%20think%20we%20both%20had%20in%20that%20scene%20is%20just%20something%20that%20can%20happen%20in%20a%20scene%20like%20that%3A%20that%20Daemon%20just%20seems%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20you're%20in%20charge%20of%20me.%20I'm%20not%20the%20Daemon%20you%20knew%2C%20I'm%20not%20the%20Daemon%20the%20fans%20knew.%26quot%3B%20I%20think%20the%20writing%20really%20is%20brave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221267%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22daenerys%20targaryen%2C%20seen%20fronm%20the%20back%20on%20a%20smoking%20plain.%20around%20her%20are%20three%20small%20dragons%2C%20drawling%20in%20her%20arms%20as%20she%20looks%20out%20towards%20an%20orange%20skyk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b0def5a5247369a3e974ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22950%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaenerys%20Targaryen%20briefly%20appears%20in%20Daemon's%20vision%20in%20the%20season%20two%20finale%20of%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20to%20dig%20into%20some%20of%20the%20meat%20of%20the%20vision%2C%20too.%20Were%20you%20involved%20in%20discussions%20about%20Daenerys%20appearing%20and%20how%20this%20played%20into%20teasing%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgame-of-thrones-azor-ahai-prophecy-theory-jon-daenerys-melisandre-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ethe%20Prince%20That%20Was%20Promised%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20sequence%20itself%2C%20I%20knew%20Daenerys%20was%20in%20it%2C%20and%20it%20was%20actually%20just%20the%20process%20for%20me%20of%20where%20does%20she%20fit%20in%20it%20so%20it%20actually%20is%20part%20of%20the%20storytelling%20of%20the%20sequence%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20we're%20just%20seeing%20her.%20And%20so%20I%20just%20kept%20building%20the%20sequence%20in%20a%20way%20that%20it%20felt%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20you're%20going%20back.%20This%20vision%20is%20telling%20you%20there%20were%20eggs%20and%20there%20was%20a%20woman%2C%20and%20from%20those%20eggs%20came%20the%20dragons.%20And%20that's%20how%20our%20dynasty%20came%20back.%20And%20that%20was%20the%20most%20important%20thing%2C%20that%20we%20were%20gone.%20It%20was%20all%20dead.%26quot%3B%20And%20that's%20when%20Daemon%20is%20walking%20across%20all%20this%20death%2C%20and%20then%20he%20falls%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20that%20was%20metaphorical%2C%20and%20I%20just%20crossed%20my%20fingers%20that%20people%20would%20feel%20it.%20They%20wouldn't%20think%20it.%20And%20something%20that%20Ryan%20really%20wanted%20was%20he%20didn't%20want%20it%20to%20feel%20connected%2C%20like%20literal.%20He%20wanted%20it%20to%20feel%20emotional.%20And%20yet%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20had%20to%20achieve%20something%20literal.%20So%20it%20was%20fantastic%20just%20going%20through%20the%20versions%20of%20it.%20The%20placement%20of%20Daenerys%20was%20quite%20intentional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20big%2C%20loud%20finale%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20staging%20a%20huge%20battle%2C%20or%20depicting%20a%20tragic%20death.%20We%20have%20these%20big%20character%20payoffs%20and%20emotional%20beats%20rather%20than%20the%20spectacle%20some%20might%20expect.%20How%20do%20you%20approach%20an%20episode%20like%20this%2C%20while%20also%20balancing%20having%20to%20deliver%20an%20element%20of%20finality%20for%20a%20season%20conclusion%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20funny%2C%20somebody%20was%20interviewing%20me%20when%20I%20did%20episode%20three%2C%20and%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan't%20wait%20for%20the%20war%20in%20episode%20eight!%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20told%20my%20husband%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20no%2C%20everybody's%20expecting%20a%20war%20episode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20just%20funny%2C%20right%3F%2