%20thousands%20of%20protesters%20defied%20curfew%2C%20marching%20on%20capital%20city%20Dhaka's%20streets%20and%20later%20stormed%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20palace%2C%20vandalising%20the%20statue%20of%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%2C%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20father%20and%20Bangladesh's%20independence%20hero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20Army%20chief%20General%20Waker-Uz-Zaman%20announced%20that%20the%20country%20would%20be%20run%20by%20an%20interim%20government.%20Student%20protesters%20have%20already%20rejected%20a%20military%20government.%20The%20Army%20chief's%20address%20was%20delayed%20as%20they%20gave%20Hasina%20time%20to%20resign%20and%20leave%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh%20worsened%20on%20August%204%20when%20at%20least%2098%20people%2C%20including%2014%20policemen%2C%20were%20killed%20and%20hundreds%20injured%20in%20fierce%20clashes%20between%20protesters%20demanding%20Hasina's%20resignation%20and%20supporters%20of%20the%20ruling%20party.%20This%20proved%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20toughest%20challenges%20for%20Hasina%2C%20who%20had%20ruled%20the%20nation%20since%202009.%20Amid%20fierce%20clashes%2C%20the%20Bangladesh%20army%20had%20imposed%20indefinite%20curfew%20and%204G%20mobile%20internet%20and%20social%20media%20platforms%20were%20shut%20down%20to%20prevent%20the%20spread%20of%20'rumours'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20harsh%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%2018%20million%20young%20people%20are%20out%20of%20work%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20has%20a%20population%20of%20170%20million.%20Bangladesh%20is%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economies%20in%20the%20world.%20The%20country%20exports%20clothes%20worth%20around%20%2440%20billion%20to%20the%20global%20market.%20The%20retail%20sector%20employs%20more%20than%204%20million%20people%2C%20including%20women.%20But%20this%20growth%20has%20not%20translated%20into%20jobs%20for%20educated%20youngsters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protests%20began%20last%20month%20following%20a%20High%20Court%20order%20to%20restore%2030%20per%20cent%20job%20quotas%20for%20descendants%20of%20freedom%20fighters.%20This%20created%20fear%20among%20the%20general%20population%2C%20which%20is%20largely%20unemployed.%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20refusal%20to%20meet%20the%20students'%20demands%2C%20citing%20court%20proceedings%2C%20escalated%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20biggest%20mistakes%20was%20her%20comment%20calling%20those%20opposing%20job%20quotas%20as%20'Razakars'%20(an%20offensive%20term%20in%20Bangladesh)%20or%20those%20who%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Pakistani%20Army%20during%20Bangladesh's%201971%20War%20of%20Independence.%20It%20was%20the%20trigger%20for%20thousands%20of%20students%20who%20came%20together%20to%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20had%20always%20accused%20Hasina%2C%20who%20won%20three%20consecutive%20elections%2C%20of%20thwarting%20free%20and%20fair%20polls.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20prevailing%20perception%20that%20'growth'%20was%20only%20helping%20those%20close%20to%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20open%20discussions%20on%20social%20media%20charging%20top%20officials%2C%20both%20serving%20and%20retired%2C%20of%20corruption.%20In%20fact%2C%20Hasina%20had%20acknowledged%20corruption%20as%20a%20problem%20and%20had%20promised%20to%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20close%20to%20Hasina%20blame%20China%20and%20Pakistan%20for%20the%20unrest%2C%20arguing%20that%20these%20countries%20wanted%20to%20end%20the%20moderate%20Islamic%20rule%20of%20Hasina%2C%20where%20they%20had%20little%20say%2C%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20parties%20promoting%20radical%20Islam%20-%20like%20the%20opposition%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20(BNP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20watchful%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20been%20closely%20monitoring%20the%20developments%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20is%20keeping%20a%20close%20watch.%20As%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20flight%20landed%20in%20Hindon%20near%20Delhi%2C%20Foreign%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20held%20consultations%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20issued%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20alert%26quot%3B%20along%20its%20border%20with%20Bangladesh%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%20India%20had%20already%20cautioned%20its%20citizens%20to%20avoid%20travelling%20to%20Bangladesh%20until%20further%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20always%20considered%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20a%20close%20friend%20in%20a%20neighbourhood%20where%20its%20army%20confronts%20both%20Pakistan%20and%20China%20along%20hostile%2C%20disputed%20borders.%20India%20shares%20a%20long%20border%20with%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20is%20also%20crucial%20to%20the%20security%20of%20India's%20remote%20northeastern%20states%2C%20where%20insurgent%20groups%20used%20to%20be%20active.%20They%20often%20took%20sanctuary%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20shares%20a%20porous%20border%20with%20some%20of%20these%20states.%20On%20Hasina's%20watch%2C%20India's%20northeastern%20border%20was%20relatively%20calm%20because%20she%20had%20not%20allowed%20Bangladesh%20to%20be%20used%20by%20insurgent%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBangladesh%20is%20our%20close%20and%20strategic%20partner.%20Hence%2C%20instability%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20has%20obvious%20diaspora%20and%20security%20imperatives%20which%20might%20already%20be%20felt.%20The%20influx%20of%20refugees%20escaping%20violence%20can%20become%20a%20problem.%20External%20powers%20inimical%20to%20India's%20interests%20may%20gain%20ground%2C%20which%20will%20have%20to%20be%20factored%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ambassador%20Anil%20Trigunayat%2C%20a%20retired%20Indian%20Foreign%20Service%20(IFS)%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrade%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20will%20also%20be%20significantly%20impacted%2C%20with%20business%20activities%20at%20Petrapole%2C%20the%20largest%20land%20port%20in%20India%20and%20South%20Asia%2C%20nearly%20coming%20to%20a%20halt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheikh%20Hasina%20had%20ably%20balanced%20ties%20with%20both%20India%20and%20China.%20During%20her%20tenure%2C%20in%20all%20its%20developmental%20partnership%20with%20China%2C%20Bangladesh%20had%20been%20heedful%20about%20India's%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20acted%20like%20a%20mediator%20between%20Bangladesh%20and%20the%20Western%20countries%2C%20who%20were%20unhappy%20with%20the%20elections%20held%20in%20Bangladesh%20in%20January%2C%20in%20which%20Hasina%20was%20re-elected%20for%20a%20fourth%20term.%20India%20had%20told%20the%20US%20that%20sidelining%20Bangladesh%20would%20mean%20giving%20China%20a%20chance%20to%20participate%20in%20Bangladesh's%20development%20and%20thereby%20a%20stake%20in%20its%20matters%2C%20which%20was%20neither%20good%20for%20India%20nor%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20prevailing%20chaos%20and%20changed%20situation%2C%20India%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20apprehensive%20about%20its%20relationship%20with%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhichever%20government%20comes%20to%20power%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20it%20will%20want%20to%20engage%20with%20India.%20Both%20the%20countries%20know%20that%20engaging%20with%20each%20other%20is%20going%20to%20give%20benefits%20to%20the%20people%20and%20that's%20what%20all%20governments%20are%20there%20for.%20There%20may%20be%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20but%20the%20governments%20of%20both%20the%20countries%20will%20engage%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sreeradha%20Datta%2C%20professor%20of%20international%20affairs%2C%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Datta%20continues%2C%20%26quot%3BSome%20aspects%20may%20not%20be%20as%20strong%20as%20it%20was%20earlier%20and%20some%20aspects%20may%20in%20fact%20improve%20also%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20issues%20like%20river%20water%20management%20still%20need%20to%20be%20sorted%20out%2C%20India-Bangladesh%20has%20seen%20wide-ranging%20collaboration%20on%20many%20other%20issues%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%20A%20substantive%20bilateral%20partnership%20in%20trade%20and%20commerce%2C%20people-to-people%20ties%2C%20defence%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20were%20the%20hallmarks%20in%20the%20golden%20era%20of%20Delhi-Dhaka%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20road%20ahead%2C%20Mr%20Trigunayat%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20ensuing%20power%20structure%20going%20forward%20and%20the%20role%20the%20army%20plays%20in%20the%20democratic%20polity%20which%20is%20usually%20preferred%20by%20people.%20India%20has%20a%20policy%20that%20is%20pro-Bangladesh%20and%20pro%20our%20neighbour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20India%20prepares%20to%20tackle%20the%20sudden%20volatility%20and%20turmoil%20in%20its%20neighbourhood%2C%20it%20will%20also%20be%20working%20towards%20a%20friendly%20government%20in%20Dhaka.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20India%20will%20keep%20a%20lookout%20for%20other%20nations%20meddling%20in%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722875760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F4hd3mvb8_bangladesh_625x300_05_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheikh-hasinas-15-year-reign-ends-impact-on-india-bangladesh-ties-6269822%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sheikh%20Hasina%20today%20resigned%20as%20Bangladesh%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20fled%20the%20country.%20As%20the%20Bangladesh%20army%20took%20control%20amid%20anarchy%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20special%20flight%20landed%20at%20an%20air%20base%20near%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheikh-hasinas-15-year-reign-ends-impact-on-india-bangladesh-ties-6269822%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.