r.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20that%20the%20river%20was%20practically%20non-existent.%20We%20could%20only%20see%20small%20%3Cem%3Epuliya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(culverts)%20that%20were%20once%20made%20over%20the%20river.%20At%20several%20points%2C%20farmers%20had%20started%20growing%20crops%20considering%20it%20to%20be%20vacant%20land.%20The%20streak%20of%20the%20river%20was%20not%20completely%20connected%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20places%2C%20the%20area%20was%20covered%20in%20small%20puddles.%20The%20river%20was%20encroached%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20it%20lost%20its%20path%20of%20natural%20flow%20downstream.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20nearby%20areas%20would%20remain%20waterlogged%20during%20monsoon.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Sot%20river%20acted%20as%20a%20natural%20drainage%20system%20for%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20the%20groundwater%20table%20had%20drastically%20reduced%20in%20the%20area%20as%20farmers%20became%20dependent%20on%20borewells%2C%20which%20further%20exacerbated%20the%20water%20problem%20in%20the%20region.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20hand%20pumps%2C%20as%20deep%20as%2050%20feet%2C%20started%20becoming%20non-functional%20because%20of%20the%20receding%20water%20table%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22When%20former%20district%20magistrate%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%20visited%20the%20field%2C%20he%20found%20there%20was%20hardly%20any%20water%20in%20the%20river.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359110%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhen%20former%20district%20magistrate%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%20visited%20the%20field%2C%20he%20found%20hardly%20any%20water%20in%20the%20river.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F357468%2Fias-officer-revive-water-table-cdo-varanasi-himanshu-nagpal-rainwater-harvesting-river-rejuvenation-groundwater-recharge%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20the%20IAS%20officer%20decided%20to%20rejuvenate%20the%20river%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20conversation%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20shares%20how%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20masterplan%20behind%20the%20river%20rejuvenation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpearheaded%20by%20Manish%2C%20the%20Sambhal%20district%20conducted%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20length%20of%20the%20river.%20The%20results%20showed%20that%20the%20Sot%20river%2C%20which%20appeared%20to%20be%20non-existent%2C%20was%20actually%20a%20110%20km%20long%20stretch%20starting%20from%20the%20Amroha%20district%20in%20the%20North%20and%20flowing%20towards%20Budaun%20in%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20administration%20conducted%20a%20survey%20to%20understand%20the%20natural%20alignment%20of%20the%20river.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20physical%20demarcation%20of%20the%20region%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20the%20river.%20The%20third%20step%20was%20to%20clear%20the%20illegal%20encroachments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20was%20to%20remove%20the%20encroachments%20along%20the%20river.%20Using%20the%20revenue%20land%20records%2C%20we%20understood%20that%20there%20were%20huge%20encroachments%20on%20the%20river%20area%20which%20had%20become%20flat%20at%20some%20points.%20Although%20there%20was%20no%20permanent%20construction%2C%20people%20started%20using%20it%20to%20grow%20crops.%20As%20it%20was%20illegal%20usage%2C%20we%20sought%20the%20help%20of%20the%20revenue%20land%20records%20team%20to%20clear%20encroachments%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20step%20was%20desilting%20of%20the%20river%20to%20remove%20fine%20silt%20and%20sediment%20collected%20in%20the%20river%20and%20restore%20it%20to%20its%20natural%20capacity.%20As%20part%20of%20this%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20roped%20in%20MGNREGA%20(Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act)%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20in%20December%202022%2C%20the%20project%20was%20completed%20in%20six%20months%20by%20June%202023.%20During%20the%20last%20monsoon%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F348157%2Fmanganga-river-solapur-rejuvenation-efforts-vaijinath-ghongade-awarded-book-parikrama-mangangechi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20river%20captured%20the%20rainwater%20and%20was%20revived%20to%20its%20old%20glory%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20region%20was%20also%20free%20from%20waterlogging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20district%20administration%20roped%20in%20MGNREGA%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359109%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20district%20administration%20roped%20MGNREGA%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20river%20has%20a%20catchment%20area.%20The%20natural%20flow%20of%20water%20in%20an%20area%20will%20be%20towards%20the%20river%2C%20so%20runoff%20water%20from%20nearby%20areas%20flows%20in%20that%20direction.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F355522%2Fwater-hero-rambabu-tiwari-mann-ki-baat-bundelkhand-drought-pond-revival-jal-mitra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIf%20the%20flow%20is%20hindered%2C%20then%20water%20gets%20logged%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20area%20but%20this%20time%2C%20this%20water%20was%20directed%20towards%20Sot%2C%E2%80%9D%20Manish%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20development%20was%20also%20followed%20by%20a%20massive%20plantation%20drive%20along%20the%20river%20bank.%20As%20many%20as%2010%2C000%20bamboo%20saplings%20were%20planted%20to%20prevent%20future%20soil%20erosion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaintaining%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20restored%20glory%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20project%20completion%2C%20it%20was%20observed%20that%20the%20seasonal%20Sot%20river%20received%20ample%20water%20in%20the%20monsoon%20and%20remained%20rejuvenated%20for%20the%20next%20two%20and%20a%20half%20months.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20project%2C%20several%20micro%20check%20dams%20were%20also%20built%20on%20the%20river%20to%20slow%20the%20runoff%20in%20the%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20this%20work%20was%20lauded%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20his%20monthly%20radio%20programme%20%E2%80%98Mann%20Ki%20Baat%E2%80%99%20in%20September%202023.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20proved%20to%20be%20very%20encouraging%20for%20all%20the%20officials%20and%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%20associated%20with%20the%20project.%20Inspired%20by%20this%2C%20the%20districts%20of%20Amroha%20and%20Budaun%20also%20undertook%20the%20project%20of%20reviving%20the%20Sot%20river%20downstream%20and%20upstream%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Within%20six%20months%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359113%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWithin%20six%20months%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManish%20credits%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project%20to%20the%20local%20people%2C%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20MGNREGA%20workers%2C%20and%20district%20officials.%20In%20June%202024%2C%20he%20was%20transferred%20to%20Saharanpur%20district%20but%20this%20did%20not%20affect%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERam%20Ashish%2C%20the%20District%20Development%20Officer%20of%20Sambhal%2C%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20keep%20monitoring%20for%20encroachments%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20river%20remains%20rejuvenated.%20Post%20monsoon%2C%20the%20soil%20erodes%20into%20the%20river.%20So%2C%20we%20are%20working%20on%20a%20plan%20to%20organise%20desiltation%20and%20continue%20the%20work%20started%20by%20Manish%20sir.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20while%20some%20downstream%20areas%20currently%20have%20water%2C%20they%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20river%20filled%20to%20the%20brim%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20when%20it%20rains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20IAS%20Manish%20was%20reached%20out%20to%20by%20residents%20of%20Saharanpur%20to%20replicate%20the%20work%20seeing%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project%20in%20Sambhal%20district.%20%E2%80%9CSaharanpur%20has%20several%20seasonal%20rivers%20such%20as%20Kali%20and%20Hindon%20rivers.%20They%20originate%20from%20Shivaliks%20and%20pass%20through%20the%20district.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20their%20area%20has%20reduced%20in%20size.%20We%20aim%20to%20work%20on%20these%20rivers%20next%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Manish%20believes%20that%20the%20administration%20can%20only%20play%20the%20role%20of%20a%20facilitator%2C%20but%20it%20is%20only%20when%20the%20community%20becomes%20the%20protector%20of%20its%20rivers%20that%20they%20can%20remain%20rejuvenated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Manish%2C%20the%20Sot%20river%20rejuvenation%20project%20during%20his%20tenure%20in%20Sambhal%20was%20extremely%20fulfilling.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20project%20was%20very%20close%20to%20my%20heart.%20Projects%20such%20as%20river%20rejuvenation%20take%20a%20backseat%20as%20they%20are%20not%20always%20a%20priority%20among%20other%20routine%20works.%20But%20if%20we%20do%20not%20rejuvenate%20these%20rivers%2C%20people%20will%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20a%20water%20crisis.%20Thankfully%2C%20the%20State%20Government%20has%20also%20been%20actively%20focusing%20on%20the%20environment%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F230547%2Fias-hero-kalyani-river-cleanup-uttar-pradesh-lockdown-jobs-methods-workers-inspiring-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereviving%20water%20bodies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20establishing%20Amrit%20Sarovar%20projects%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Khushi%20Arora%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Ram%20Ashish.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722426607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D359103%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sot%20River%2C%20once%20the%20lifeline%20of%20Sambhal%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20lost%20its%20natural%20flow%20due%20to%20decades%20of%20encroachment.%20Here's%20how%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%2C%20along%20with%20officials%20and%20locals%2C%20revived%20the%20110-km%20stretch%2C%20restoring%20water%20flow%20and%20eliminating%20waterlogging.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A52%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F359103%2Fias-officer-sot-river-revival-rejuvenation-project-sambhal-uttar-pradesh-manish-bansal-mgnrega-gram-panchayat-monsoon-waterlogging%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Designer%20Employs%20Artisan%20Families%20To%20Handcraft%20Brass%2C%20Copper%20Kitchenware%3B%20Earns%20Rs%2036%20Cr%2FYear%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20find%20their%20calling%20early%20in%20life%20and%20remain%20dedicated%20to%20their%20childhood%20dreams%20of%20becoming%20doctors%2C%20teachers%2C%20and%20more.%20However%2C%20for%20some%2C%20discovering%20their%20passion%20takes%20time%20and%20multiple%20attempts.%20This%20was%20true%20for%20Kirti%20Goel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20life%20decisions%2C%20teachers%20and%20mentors%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20shaping%20our%20paths.%20For%20Kirti%2C%20a%20teacher%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%20to%20explore%20something%20artistic%20set%20her%20on%20a%20journey%20that%20eventually%20led%20her%20to%20head%20a%20multi-crore%20company%20%E2%80%94%20contributing%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F257070%2Fkerala-puppet-dying-art-heritage-nokkuvidya-pavakkali-padma-shri-moozhikkal-pankajakshi-granddaughter-renjini-india-ana79%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreserving%20a%20dying%20art%20form%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhile%20supporting%20a%20community%20of%20artists%20and%20craftsmen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Kirti%2C%2028%2C%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20%E2%80%98P-TAL%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20an%20Amritsar-based%20business%20that%20sells%20traditional%20handcrafted%20kitchenware%2C%20dinnerware%2C%20and%20tableware%20made%20of%20brass%2C%20copper%2C%20and%20bronze.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20brand%20is%20not%20just%20about%20kitchenware%3B%20it%20is%20also%20dedicated%20to%20helping%20the%20Thathera%20community%20preserve%20the%20art%20of%20making%20these%20utensils%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kirti%20tells%3Cstrong%3E%20The%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Her%20company%20recently%20featured%20on%20Shark%20Tank%20India%2C%20where%20she%20was%20able%20to%20bag%20an%20%E2%80%98all-shark%E2%80%99%20deal!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20story%20of%20finding%20her%20passion%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20simple%20suggestion%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20me%20choosing%20a%20career%20path%20was%20quite%20difficult.%20Most%20of%20my%20friends%20were%20going%20to%20opt%20for%20engineering%20and%20so%20did%20I.%20But%20soon%20enough%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20it%20was%20not%20for%20me.%20However%2C%20I%20was%20sure%20about%20one%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20different%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kirti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20a%20teacher%20suggested%20that%20she%20try%20something%20more%20artistic%20and%20go%20for%20designing.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20why%2C%20but%20when%20she%20suggested%20it%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20maybe%20it%20was%20indeed%20worth%20a%20try.%20So%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20apply%20to%20Pearl%20Academy.%20Luckily%2C%20I%20got%20in%2C%20and%20it%20paved%20the%20way%20forward%20for%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CI%20started%20to%20think%20more%20creatively%20and%20feel%20that%20I%20was%20where%20I%20belonged.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20second%20year%20in%20training%2C%20she%20worked%20on%20a%20project%20based%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F57220%2Fjourney-indian-handicraft-landscape%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20crafts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%20got%20to%20work%20with%20%3Cem%3EChamba%20Rumal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(an%20embroidered%20handkerchief%20with%20detailed%20patterns%20in%20bright%20and%20pleasing%20colour%20schemes)%20artists%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20riveting%20experience.%20I%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised%20at%20how%20rich%20the%20handmade%20crafts%20of%20India%20are%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kirit%20Goel%2C%20Founder%20of%20P-TAL%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-50-1721396333-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357791%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKirit%20Goel%2C%20Founder%20of%20P-TAL%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20Kirti%20feels%20that%20the%20project%20was%20the%20key%20foundation%20stone%20that%20paved%20her%20path%20for%20P-TAL.%20%E2%80%9CI%20started%20to%20research%20more%20crafts%20and%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20UNESCO-certified%20craft%2C%20%3Cem%3EThathera%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20art%2C%20I%20found%2C%20was%20disappearing%20as%20there%20was%20not%20much%20demand%20in%20the%20market%20for%20it%20or%20so%20was%20the%20general%20notion%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThathera%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecraft%20involves%20making%20traditional%20brass%20and%20copper%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F281408%2Ftraditional-indian-cookware-clay-cast-iron-brass-copper-amazon-buy-online%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekitchen%20utensils%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20hand.%20The%20word%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ethathera%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20means%20%E2%80%98the%20beater%E2%80%99%2C%20describing%20the%20act%20of%20beating%20the%20metal%20to%20transform%20it%20into%20desired%20shapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELearning%20about%20the%20craft%20motivated%20me%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20good%20at%20my%20academy%20but%20I%20knew%20that%20the%20fashion%20market%20was%20highly%20saturated.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20was%20also%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%20for%20me%20to%20save%20the%20dying%20art%20of%20my%20country.%20So%2C%20I%20took%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%20and%20lunged%20into%20starting%20P-Tal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EP-TAL%20was%20founded%20in%202016.%20Talking%20about%20what%20went%20behind%20it%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirst%20things%20first%2C%20I%20got%20started%20on%20the%20market%20research%20and%20kept%20going%20back%20and%20forth%20with%20consultants%20and%20product%20designers%20to%20understand%20what%20the%20consumer%20needs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EConnecting%20with%20craftspersons%20and%20reviving%20the%20art%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20perception%20in%20the%20market%20that%20the%20artisans%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20find%20as%20most%20of%20them%20had%20switched%20careers%2C%20shares%20Kirti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20delved%20deeper%2C%20we%20discovered%20that%20this%20craft%20isn%E2%80%99t%20confined%20to%20just%20one%20location.%20In%20Jaipur%2C%20Moradabad%2C%20Lucknow%2C%20and%20Dehradun%2C%20there%20are%20%3Cem%3EThatheras%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Once%2C%20every%20village%20had%20artisans%20crafting%20brass%20and%20copper%20utensils.%20However%2C%20many%20shifted%20to%20producing%20aluminium%20items%20as%20brass%20and%20copper%20became%20more%20expensive%20and%20demand%20declined.%20The%20artisans%20struggled%20to%20innovate%20with%20these%20materials%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20traditional%20craft%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CFinding%20artisans%20and%20understanding%20their%20needs%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20difficult.%20We%20identified%20artisans%20and%20collaborated%20with%20them.%E2%80%9D%20Working%20with%20P-TAL%20has%20since%20significantly%20improved%20their%20earnings%20from%20about%20Rs%2020%20per%20hour%20to%20Rs%20150%20per%20hour%2C%20she%20further%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20his%20work%20before%20collaborating%20with%20P-Tal%2C%20Mandeep%20Singh%20(35)%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20hard%20work.%20The%20art%20is%20a%20complex%20process%20that%20involves%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20skilled%20handiwork%2C%20but%20many%20people%20do%20not%20understand%20its%20value.%20Declining%20sales%20led%20to%20less%20and%20less%20work%20each%20year.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20our%20children%20to%20follow%20in%20this%20trade.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20things%20took%20a%20positive%20turn%20three%20years%20ago%20when%20P-Tal%20approached%20him.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20we%20have%20work%20365%20days%20a%20year.%20P-Tal%20has%20been%20dedicated%20to%20revitalising%20the%20art%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20a%20shift%20towards%20using%20copper%20and%20brass.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20we%20have%20more%20clients%20and%20are%20earning%20better.%20If%20our%20children%20want%20to%20learn%20the%20art%20now%2C%20we%20would%20encourage%20them%2C%20as%20it%20is%20now%20more%20financially%20stable%20than%20ever%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20company%20sells%2080%20varieties%20of%20kitchenware%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562.jpg%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562-500x261.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562-768x401.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-51-1-1721396562-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357792%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20company%20sells%2080%20varieties%20of%20kitchenware%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20observed%20the%20artisans%E2%80%99%20work%20and%20how%20they%20were%20making%20utensils%2C%20and%20I%20realised%20something%20important%3A%20when%20you%20need%20to%20innovate%20a%20craft%2C%20you%20have%20to%20immerse%20yourself%20in%20it%20completely%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kirti%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20previously%20worked%20with%20craft%20clusters%2C%20she%20understood%20the%20process%20of%20collaborating%20with%20artisans.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20started%20working%20with%20them%20and%20learned%20about%20their%20skills%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20I%20had%20to%20adapt%20to%20their%20expertise%20to%20develop%20new%20products.%20One%20of%20our%20first%20new%20designs%20was%20a%20%3Cem%3Eparat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20traditional%20flat%2C%20round%20utensil).%20We%20simply%20added%20a%20clock%20to%20the%20back%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eparat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20making%20it%20a%20functional%20and%20decorative%20piece.%20This%20design%20was%20easy%20for%20them%20to%20make%20because%20they%20were%20already%20accustomed%20to%20crafting%20%3Cem%3Eparats%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20initial%20days%20of%20her%20product%20making%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20very%20interesting%20for%20me%20as%20a%20designer%20to%20work%20with%20their%20skills%2C%20understand%20the%20market%2C%20and%20create%20something%20in%20collaboration%20that%20the%20market%20needed.%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20learning%20and%20unlearning%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKirti%20says%20the%20products%20started%20to%20gain%20popularity%20after%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit%20and%20people%20started%20to%20turn%20towards%20traditional%20and%20sustainable%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20attended%20exhibitions%20and%20gathered%20customer%20feedback.%20Through%20conversations%20and%20our%20experiences%2C%20we%20realised%20that%20during%20our%20first%20year%2C%20people%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fully%20understand%20our%20products.%20However%2C%20after%20about%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%2C%20we%20began%20to%20notice%20a%20genuine%20interest%20in%20purchasing%20our%20cookware%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20company%20produces%20over%2080%20types%20of%20products%20in%20kitchenware%2C%20dinnerware%20and%20tableware%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3Eparats%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20flat%20plate-like%20utensil%20used%20to%20kneed%20dough)%2C%20drinking%20glasses%2C%20tumblers%2C%20brass%20ladles%2C%20copper%20baking%20trays%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20collaborates%20with%20about%2050%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F296802%2Fdesigner-helps-weaver-families-revive-bandhej-brand-heritage-prints-clothing-kutch%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamilies%20of%20artisans%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20sources%20their%20products.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20place%20orders%20with%20the%20artisans%2C%20and%20once%20the%20items%20are%20completed%2C%20we%20procure%20them.%20Depending%20on%20the%20volume%20of%20work%2C%20a%20craftsperson%20working%20with%20us%20can%20earn%20between%20Rs%2025%2C000%20and%20Rs%2050%2C000%20a%20month%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kirti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-versio